<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ901227-0038</DOCNO><DOCID>901227-0038.</DOCID><HL>   Hotel Investors Corp.   And Trust Receive   Acquisition Proposal</HL><DATE>12/27/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17</SO><CO>   HOT</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)REAL ESTATE INVESTMENTS (REA)</IN><LP>   BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. -- Investor Leonard M. Ross said hehas proposed to buy all the shares of Hotel Investors Trustand Hotel Investors Corp. for $13.7 million.   Mr. Ross currently owns 9.8%, or a 1,190,400 share stakein the companies, which are paired and trade together on theNew York Stock Exchange.</LP><TEXT>   In composite trading on the New York Stock Exchangeyesterday, Hotel Investors Trust and Hotel Investors Corp.shares closed at $1.625, up 50 cents.   In a Dec. 21 letter attached to a Securities and ExchangeCommission filing, Mr. Ross said that the proposal wouldconsist of a merger between Rossco Holdings Inc. or a newlyorganized corporation to be formed by him, called Newco, andHotel Investors.   Under the merger proposal, holders of the paired shareswould receive $1.25 a share in cash and the stock of a newlyformed subsidiary, the Nevada Corp., into which all of theassets associated with hotel and gambling properties would beplaced free and clear of mortgage debt. According to thefiling, the stock to be received would be registered.   Earlier this month, Hotel Investors Trust, a real estateinvestment trust based in Los Angeles, suffered a series ofsetbacks in its long effort to sell most of its hotels toPark Plaza Inc., a unit of EIE International Corp. of Japan.Park Plaza told Hotel Investors that it was unlikely tocomplete the sale because of financing problems.</TEXT></DOC>